From a38db4b63c2a0e1c19e71a1e4bfba39e2878d662 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jun Zeng <jun1.zeng@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 29 Sep 2025 20:40:22 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Adaptive NVME SSD interrupt coalescing

This is to solve NVME SSD interrupt burst:
If SSD queue is almost full, enable coalescing interrupt.
If SSD queue is almost empty, disable coalescing interrupt.

Just need to apply the patch to Linux kernel, and generally nothing more
needed to configure.

Signed-off-by: Liang Fang <liang.a.fang@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jun Zeng <jun1.zeng@intel.com>
---
